48
00:07:51,220 --> 00:07:52,820
But it suddenly received
these coordinates.

49
00:07:53,340 --> 00:07:54,300
I don't think

50
00:07:54,900 --> 00:07:56,180
the clue would dry up so easily.

51
00:07:58,260 --> 00:07:58,700
Shang,

52
00:07:59,220 --> 00:08:00,140
help me investigate further.

53
00:08:01,100 --> 00:08:02,060
I won't give up on the search

54
00:08:02,940 --> 00:08:03,820
for Xu Jingyang.

55
00:08:07,780 --> 00:08:08,460
Lady,

56
00:08:09,740 --> 00:08:11,140
couldn't you wait for me to clean up?

57
00:08:11,420 --> 00:08:12,820
The tissues cost money, you know?

58
00:08:14,500 --> 00:08:15,420
Plain rice has no flavor,

59
00:08:16,140 --> 00:08:17,300
won't you order something else?

60
00:08:18,860 --> 00:08:19,420
Weirdo.

61
00:08:24,820 --> 00:08:25,180
Oh, also,

62
00:08:26,140 --> 00:08:27,140
help me check

63
00:08:27,820 --> 00:08:28,700
what happened

64
00:08:28,700 --> 00:08:29,580
to Jiang Xiaoyuan in Chongqing.

65
00:08:30,500 --> 00:08:31,540
She's deliberately pretending

66
00:08:31,540 --> 00:08:32,060
not to know me now

67
00:08:33,100 --> 00:08:34,740
and she's still as bad-tempered as before.

68
00:08:41,820 --> 00:08:43,980
♪Can you hear me?♪

69
00:08:44,300 --> 00:08:48,260
♪Walking through the misty forest♪

70
00:08:48,860 --> 00:08:53,860
♪I forgot our past embraces♪

71
00:08:53,860 --> 00:08:57,940
♪And promises♪

72
00:08:59,300 --> 00:09:01,820
♪Can you hear me?♪

73
00:09:02,020 --> 00:09:06,020
♪In dreams where you reside♪

74
00:09:07,620 --> 00:09:08,820
(It turns out being hungry)

75
00:09:08,820 --> 00:09:09,980
(feels this terrible.)

76
00:09:11,780 --> 00:09:13,300
(Now, even a bowl of rice)

77
00:09:13,300 --> 00:09:14,900
(tastes so delicious to me.)

78
00:09:15,860 --> 00:09:17,140
(If I were with my dad,)

79
00:09:17,540 --> 00:09:19,180
(how could I possibly starve?)

80
00:09:19,940 --> 00:09:21,060
(And how dare these people)

81
00:09:21,060 --> 00:09:22,540
(talk to me like this?)

82
00:09:25,300 --> 00:09:27,100
(Now that I have no one to rely on,)

83
00:09:29,420 --> 00:09:30,700
(what should I do?)

84
00:09:34,220 --> 00:09:36,900
♪Can you hear me?♪

85
00:09:36,900 --> 00:09:40,900
♪I can only watch you leave♪

86
00:09:41,340 --> 00:09:45,260
♪Like a vow yet to complete♪

87
00:09:45,900 --> 00:09:49,980
♪To be fulfilled with the future♪

88
00:10:03,620 --> 00:10:04,300
(I should)

89
00:10:04,340 --> 00:10:05,420
(find a job as soon as possible.)

90
00:10:07,060 --> 00:10:08,700
(I can only rely on myself now.)

91
00:10:11,260 --> 00:10:12,540
(I have to find a way
to make some money.)

92
00:10:13,460 --> 00:10:15,180
(Otherwise,
I'll have to starve tomorrow.)

93
00:10:21,660 --> 00:10:22,260
Give it back.

94
00:10:22,500 --> 00:10:23,100
Don't do that!

95
00:10:25,740 --> 00:10:26,620
Give me!

96
00:10:27,740 --> 00:10:28,500
What are you doing?

97
00:10:29,980 --> 00:10:30,580
Give it back!

98
00:10:34,500 --> 00:10:35,140
Stop!

99
00:10:35,980 --> 00:10:37,180
- Move out of the way!
- Run!

100
00:10:38,700 --> 00:10:39,300
Stop!

101
00:10:39,500 --> 00:10:40,060
Make way!

102
00:10:41,580 --> 00:10:42,380
Stop, don't run!

103
00:10:45,380 --> 00:10:46,100
Let go!

104
00:10:49,940 --> 00:10:50,460
Are you alright?

105
00:10:53,380 --> 00:10:53,860
Let's go.

106
00:11:08,420 --> 00:11:09,180
Why do you

107
00:11:09,300 --> 00:11:10,300
keep following me?

108
00:11:12,820 --> 00:11:13,700
Do you find me funny

109
00:11:13,740 --> 00:11:14,700
in this state?

110
00:11:36,740 --> 00:11:37,540
What's this about?

111
00:11:39,140 --> 00:11:40,100
Are you pitying me?

112
00:11:45,460 --> 00:11:46,300
It's already ten.

113
00:11:47,340 --> 00:11:48,260
This area is full of dangers.

114
00:11:49,380 --> 00:11:50,540
Go find a place to stay.

115
00:11:54,500 --> 00:11:56,020
I'm asking you if you pity me.

116
00:12:03,940 --> 00:12:05,180
Do you think you're pitiable?

117
00:12:08,500 --> 00:12:10,140
We just met today.

118
00:12:11,540 --> 00:12:13,300
Whether I'm pitiable or not
is none of your business.

119
00:12:14,260 --> 00:12:15,260
Are you insane?

120
00:12:16,060 --> 00:12:16,980
At this point,

121
00:12:17,020 --> 00:12:18,140
you're still pretending not to know me.

122
00:12:20,340 --> 00:12:20,740
Yes,

123
00:12:22,100 --> 00:12:23,780
I'm insane for meddling in your affairs.

124
00:12:25,380 --> 00:12:26,740
But you better think clearly.

125
00:12:27,500 --> 00:12:28,500
Without my help,

126
00:12:29,620 --> 00:12:31,100
how will you survive tonight?

127
00:13:51,580 --> 00:13:52,740
How do I pay you back?

128
00:13:56,940 --> 00:13:57,380
No need.

129
00:13:57,820 --> 00:13:58,460
No way.

130
00:13:58,620 --> 00:13:59,940
I don't owe people favors,

131
00:14:00,260 --> 00:14:01,220
nor do I need charity.

132
00:14:04,860 --> 00:14:06,340
Then call your dad's number.

133
00:14:08,460 --> 00:14:09,780
Are you taking advantage of me?

134
00:14:14,020 --> 00:14:19,300
[Dream Mansion Hotel]

135
00:14:19,300 --> 00:14:19,660
Hello.

136
00:14:20,820 --> 00:14:21,260
Hello.

137
00:14:22,620 --> 00:14:24,060
What's the cheapest room?

138
00:14:26,100 --> 00:14:27,340
The cheapest is a standard room,

139
00:14:27,420 --> 00:14:27,980
200 a night.

140
00:14:28,580 --> 00:14:29,540
Check out

141
00:14:29,620 --> 00:14:30,140
before noon tomorrow.

142
00:14:31,740 --> 00:14:32,260
Does it include breakfast?

143
00:14:33,740 --> 00:14:34,220
Breakfast

144
00:14:34,420 --> 00:14:34,860
is separate,

145
00:14:35,020 --> 00:14:35,580
10 yuan per person.

146
00:14:37,500 --> 00:14:38,420
(So when I wake up,)

147
00:14:38,460 --> 00:14:39,500
(I'll be hungry again.)

148
00:14:40,980 --> 00:14:42,140
(He could have)

149
00:14:42,980 --> 00:14:44,340
(given me another hundred.)

150
00:14:49,060 --> 00:14:49,820
Excuse me,

151
00:14:50,660 --> 00:14:51,620
are you checking in?

152
00:14:54,140 --> 00:14:55,260
Are you hiring?

153
00:14:57,860 --> 00:14:58,540
We're not.

154
00:15:14,260 --> 00:15:16,180
[Internet cafe hiring,]

155
00:15:16,180 --> 00:15:19,500
[recruiting administrator,
room and board included]

156
00:15:20,420 --> 00:15:21,780
Isn't that a hiring notice?

157
00:15:24,020 --> 00:15:25,220
That's for the internet cafe

158
00:15:25,260 --> 00:15:25,900
behind our hotel.

159
00:15:26,260 --> 00:15:26,780
Miss,

160
00:15:26,780 --> 00:15:27,700
let me tell you,

161
00:15:27,940 --> 00:15:28,700
our hotel is already

162
00:15:28,780 --> 00:15:29,660
the best value

163
00:15:29,700 --> 00:15:30,700
in this street.

164
00:15:31,340 --> 00:15:32,020
Are you staying or not?

165
00:15:34,780 --> 00:15:35,660
No.

166
00:16:03,500 --> 00:16:03,980
Hello?

167
00:16:04,900 --> 00:16:05,460
Lian,

168
00:16:06,300 --> 00:16:07,860
she refused to stay and ran off.

169
00:16:08,700 --> 00:16:09,420
Why didn't she stay?

170
00:16:10,180 --> 00:16:11,740
She complained
that it didn't include breakfast.

171
00:16:13,220 --> 00:16:14,500
Then you should have included it.

172
00:16:15,220 --> 00:16:15,780
No, it's not that.

173
00:16:16,500 --> 00:16:17,500
You said not to blow our cover,

174
00:16:17,620 --> 00:16:18,940
and to treat her as a regular guest.

175
00:16:19,020 --> 00:16:19,820
Our regular guests

176
00:16:19,860 --> 00:16:20,780
don't get breakfast included.

177
00:16:22,380 --> 00:16:23,220
Where is she now?

178
00:16:23,780 --> 00:16:24,260
She ran off.

179
00:16:25,980 --> 00:16:26,740
She seemed interested

180
00:16:26,780 --> 00:16:27,980
in the internet cafe's job posting.

181
00:16:29,540 --> 00:16:30,260
I'm heading there now.

182
00:16:38,020 --> 00:16:39,460
[Internet Cafe]

183
00:16:39,460 --> 00:16:44,860
[Hiring]

184
00:17:08,220 --> 00:17:09,260
Is this the hiring office?

185
00:17:15,940 --> 00:17:17,700
You're coming
for an interview dressed like that?

186
00:17:23,820 --> 00:17:24,820
Are they hiring an administrator?

187
00:17:25,380 --> 00:17:26,100
Just get in line.

188
00:17:37,660 --> 00:17:38,100
Lian.

189
00:17:39,500 --> 00:17:40,260
Any luck? Did you find her?

190
00:17:41,020 --> 00:17:41,660
Didn't you say she came here

191
00:17:41,660 --> 00:17:42,460
to apply for a job?

192
00:17:42,900 --> 00:17:44,140
The boss said no one came.

193
00:17:45,220 --> 00:17:46,460
Maybe she went to the wrong place.

194
00:17:52,220 --> 00:17:53,060
Check over there.

195
00:17:54,100 --> 00:17:54,500
Okay.

196
00:18:02,500 --> 00:18:03,340
Sir, hello.

197
00:18:05,260 --> 00:18:07,020
Show me some talent.

198
00:18:07,380 --> 00:18:08,460
What can you do?

199
00:18:08,740 --> 00:18:09,540
I can do a bit of everything.

200
00:18:10,020 --> 00:18:10,700
Sing me a song.

201
00:18:14,380 --> 00:18:14,700
♪Love♪

202
00:18:15,700 --> 00:18:16,180
♪Love♪

203
00:18:17,020 --> 00:18:17,980
♪Love, love♪

204
00:18:21,100 --> 00:18:24,220
♪Love till I die♪

205
00:18:24,420 --> 00:18:27,820
♪It's not love
if you don't give it all out♪

206
00:18:28,780 --> 00:18:29,900
Okay, that's enough.

207
00:18:42,460 --> 00:18:44,180
You look nice.

208
00:18:46,380 --> 00:18:47,260
Can you dance?

209
00:18:50,620 --> 00:18:52,380
Something hot.

210
00:18:53,300 --> 00:18:54,020
Hot?

211
00:18:55,540 --> 00:18:56,620
Hot, like...

212
00:19:22,660 --> 00:19:23,300
Yeah, that'll do.

213
00:19:23,980 --> 00:19:24,660
Alright.

214
00:19:25,900 --> 00:19:26,460
You're hired.

215
00:19:27,700 --> 00:19:28,300
Pretty looks

216
00:19:28,780 --> 00:19:29,380
matter the most.

217
00:19:30,620 --> 00:19:31,420
So

218
00:19:31,740 --> 00:19:32,580
you come to work tomorrow.

219
00:19:33,180 --> 00:19:33,940
Remember

220
00:19:35,220 --> 00:19:35,940
to dress sexily.

221
00:19:36,620 --> 00:19:37,380
Why does an Internet cafe administrator

222
00:19:37,380 --> 00:19:38,300
have to dress sexily?

223
00:19:39,740 --> 00:19:40,460
Cafe administrator?

224
00:19:42,340 --> 00:19:43,500
You came to apply
as a Cafe administrator?

225
00:19:45,580 --> 00:19:46,660
Didn't you see the sign

226
00:19:46,740 --> 00:19:47,740
at the door?

227
00:19:48,340 --> 00:19:49,060
What sign?

228
00:19:50,620 --> 00:19:52,740
We're hiring live streamers,

229
00:19:53,620 --> 00:19:54,340
internet celebrities.

230
00:19:55,380 --> 00:19:56,380
You know what they are?

231
00:20:02,260 --> 00:20:03,140
One-night trial.

232
00:20:03,580 --> 00:20:04,940
If you can last

233
00:20:04,980 --> 00:20:05,820
from 8 PM tonight

234
00:20:06,020 --> 00:20:06,980
to 8 AM tomorrow morning,

235
00:20:07,260 --> 00:20:08,580
then you're officially hired.

236
00:20:09,140 --> 00:20:09,660
For power outage,

237
00:20:09,980 --> 00:20:10,660
call this number.

238
00:20:11,980 --> 00:20:13,460
If a customer's computer breaks,

239
00:20:13,620 --> 00:20:14,060
get them another one

240
00:20:14,980 --> 00:20:15,700
and report for repair.

241
00:20:16,380 --> 00:20:17,060
Got it?

242
00:20:18,940 --> 00:20:20,260
Okay, start working.

243
00:20:21,580 --> 00:20:22,620
How much is the salary?

244
00:20:23,380 --> 00:20:24,940
1,500 a month.

245
00:20:25,780 --> 00:20:26,940
Isn't that too little?

246
00:20:27,620 --> 00:20:28,660
It's even below

247
00:20:28,660 --> 00:20:29,580
the minimum wage standard.

248
00:20:30,100 --> 00:20:31,180
If it's too little,

249
00:20:31,660 --> 00:20:32,220
go find another job.

250
00:20:34,060 --> 00:20:34,900
Does it include room and board?

251
00:20:35,220 --> 00:20:35,740
Yes, it does.

252
00:20:36,420 --> 00:20:37,980
Three cup noodles a day,

253
00:20:38,500 --> 00:20:39,300
anything more is on you.

254
00:20:40,660 --> 00:20:42,460
I have to eat instant noodles all day?

255
00:20:43,500 --> 00:20:44,820
If you find it too cheap,

256
00:20:45,900 --> 00:20:46,460
then find another job.

257
00:20:49,140 --> 00:20:51,620
If you want better meals,

258
00:20:52,180 --> 00:20:53,620
you can go to my place...

259
00:21:00,460 --> 00:21:01,980
For prices and top-up,

260
00:21:02,300 --> 00:21:02,940
just follow these instructions.

261
00:21:03,900 --> 00:21:05,500
Don't touch the money
in the cash register.

262
00:21:06,540 --> 00:21:07,220
Because

263
00:21:09,180 --> 00:21:10,300
I can see

264
00:21:10,980 --> 00:21:12,340
every move you make.

265
00:21:12,820 --> 00:21:13,300
Sir.

266
00:21:14,900 --> 00:21:15,820
Clean this up

267
00:21:15,980 --> 00:21:16,940
and bring two beers.

268
00:21:17,380 --> 00:21:18,100
Okay, coming right up.

269
00:21:21,580 --> 00:21:22,300
Hurry up.

270
00:21:24,940 --> 00:21:25,820
Go.

271
00:21:43,740 --> 00:21:44,940
Are you blind?

272
00:21:46,860 --> 00:21:47,820
Sorry, sorry.

273
00:21:47,900 --> 00:21:48,300
What's this about?

274
00:21:48,340 --> 00:21:48,740
I'm sorry.

275
00:21:49,020 --> 00:21:50,220
She's new here, brand new.

276
00:21:50,380 --> 00:21:51,020
Clean it up.

277
00:21:51,140 --> 00:21:51,860
Alright, doing it right now.

278
00:21:52,420 --> 00:21:53,620
Beers, man, my treat!

279
00:21:55,380 --> 00:21:56,180
Clean it up now.

280
00:21:57,620 --> 00:21:58,900
Why did you hire her?

281
00:21:59,020 --> 00:21:59,780
I'm on it.

282
00:22:00,700 --> 00:22:01,700
Hurry up.

283
00:22:02,140 --> 00:22:02,860
Really sorry about that.

284
00:22:02,900 --> 00:22:03,300
My apologies.

285
00:22:06,340 --> 00:22:06,980
She's new here.

286
00:22:08,260 --> 00:22:09,820
Be careful, "brand new".

287
00:22:15,020 --> 00:22:16,100
Good-looking but useless.

288
00:22:17,020 --> 00:22:18,060
If it weren't for your looks,

289
00:22:18,220 --> 00:22:18,980
I wouldn't have hired you.

290
00:22:21,700 --> 00:22:22,060
Oh, right,

291
00:22:23,620 --> 00:22:24,060
your ID card.

292
00:22:25,620 --> 00:22:26,740
Why do you need my ID?

293
00:22:28,620 --> 00:22:29,580
What if you run off

294
00:22:30,180 --> 00:22:31,340
